==English==
===Etymology===
From Hindustani [[देसी]] / {{URchar|[[دیسی]]}}  (national).

===Pronunciation===
/dey-see/
===Adjective===
'''desi'''
# [[Indian]],(South Asian in general)

===Usage notes===
*For South Asians abroad, it has become a term that mainly identifies an other fellow Indians.

:''e.g.'': Desi food refers to South Asian food like rice, daal, chappati etc.
Desi dance can refer to the popular dances in the movies to Punjabi dance, ''[[Bhangra]]'' to classical dances like Bharathnatya, Kuchipudi etc.

